text:
JUST IN: President Trump’s physician said in a statement Saturday that "he is no longer considered a transmission risk to others.” 

The statement does not say when Trump’s last negative test was, or whether he is still testing positive. https://t.co/px1C9Dvvdi

text: Some doctors took to Twitter after President Trump’s physician said he is “no longer considered a transmission risk to others." Eric Topol, a physician and scientist in La Jolla, described the statement as a “master class in the art of medical deception.” https://t.co/fia394LTqi

text: Derelict boats have long been a problem in the delta. Leaking fuel, oil and metals pose a threat to rivers and sloughs that provide water to the farms of the San Joaquin Valley and close to 30 million people from the Bay Area to Southern California. https://t.co/Co3BQV26r2
